Ex. No: 13 — Reshape Data using melt() and pivot() Functions in Pandas
Aim

To reshape data using melt() and pivot() functions.

Theory

melt() converts wide data into long format.
pivot() converts long format back into wide format.


Software / Tools Required
•
Python 3.x
•
Anaconda Distribution
•
Jupyter Notebook / IDLE / Google Colab
•
Pandas Library

Program
import pandas as pd

# Creating DataFrame
data = {
    'Name': ['Ravi', 'Anu', 'Kumar'],
    'Maths': [85, 90, 78],
    'Science': [88, 92, 80]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)

print("Original DataFrame:")
print(df)

# Melt function
melted_df = pd.melt(df,
                    id_vars=['Name'],
                    var_name='Subject',
                    value_name='Marks')

print("\nMelted DataFrame:")
print(melted_df)

# Pivot function
pivoted_df = melted_df.pivot(index='Name',
                             columns='Subject',
                             values='Marks')

print("\nPivoted DataFrame:")
print(pivoted_df)



